          <analysis>
            <group_id_list>
              <group_id>O1</group_id>
              <group_id>O2</group_id>
            </group_id_list>
            <groups_desc>We tested for a difference in the mean total knowledge score between the decision aid and control groups using independent t-test (2 sided). With 100 patients in each arm, the study had more than 90% power to detect a 10% difference in knowledge assuming a common standard deviation of 18%.</groups_desc>
            <non_inferiority_type>Superiority or Other</non_inferiority_type>
            <p_value>0.01</p_value>
            <method>t-test, 2 sided</method>
            <param_type>Mean Difference (Net)</param_type>
            <param_value>3.42</param_value>
            <dispersion_type>Standard Deviation</dispersion_type>
            <dispersion_value>1.6</dispersion_value>
